# Inventory / Marketplace MVP

Internal inventory is the **source of truth**, integrated with marketplaces. **Adapter-first**: LAZADA is
the live-validated real adapter for listing import, stock-write AND **order pull** (`LazadaOrderAdapter`,
wired + paired-test-validated 2026-06; field shapes still flagged VERIFY); SHOPEE and TOKOPEDIA (= TikTok
Shop Open API v202309) have env-gated real listing/stock adapter scaffolds (NOT live-verified) and still use
the **stub** for order pull; all fall back to the Dev/stub when their app creds are unset.
Org-scoped (`organizationId`), internal-first. Roadmap + locked decisions:
`docs/roadmap/inventory-mvp.md` + the order-pull design `docs/roadmap/lazada-order-pull.md`.

## Modules & domains
- **catalog** — Product / ProductVariant (master). Server service owns Prisma (no repository).
  A product has **0..N** variants (create-without-variant is allowed; add them later from the detail
  page). The **variant is the SKU/stock leaf** (`@@unique([userId, sku])`); **`variantGroup String?`**
  is an optional grouping **label** above it — a variant is EITHER a **standalone SKU** OR a **named
  group of subvariant SKUs** (siblings share one `variantGroup`, e.g. group "iPhone 16" → "Hitam"/
  "Putih"). Grouping is **display-only**: stock/ledger/orders/sales/PO/marketplace all stay at the leaf
  — there is NO deeper stock-bearing level. Builders share `components/variant-blocks-field.tsx`
  (`VariantBlocksField` via `useFormContext`) in the create + add-variant + add-subvariant dialogs;
  `utils/variants.ts` owns `buildVariantBlocks` (group/standalone layout), `suggestVariantSku`
  (vowel-strip compaction, wand button), `formatVariantLabel` ("group · name"). Variant carries
  `cost`/`weight`, `lowStockThreshold`/`alertEnabled`, reorder planning `leadTimeDays?`/`minOrderQty?`
  (0 in the UI = unset → null), and a **per-variant photo** `imageKey?`/`imageUrl?` (separate PUBLIC R2
  bucket — see Gotchas). Variants are editable: `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId` →
  `updateVariant` (create/add-variant forms stay short; advanced planning is set later via Edit).
  Bulk add: `POST /products/:id/variants` `{ variants:[] }` → `addVariants` (all leaves in one tx).
  Stock changes go through the inventory service, NEVER by writing inventory tables from catalog.
  **Delete** (soft, `deletedAt`) of a product / variant / whole group is **guarded by a cross-module
  preflight** `getDeletionBlockers` (`GET /products/:id/deletion-blockers?variantIds=`): **BLOCKED** when
  any active variant is marketplace-mapped, has `reserved>0` or `incoming>0`, or has an open (PENDING)
  return; **WARNS** (still allowed) on available on-hand + damaged stock + **bundle membership** (names the
  bundles it's a component of + how many would empty); pending unpaid orders ignored.
  Soft-delete mangles the SKU (`archivedSku` → `<sku>::deleted::<id>`; `unarchiveSku` reverses it) so it
  **frees for reuse** (the unique index spans archived rows; safe — Sale/Order items snapshot sku).
  **Restore IS supported**: product detail has a collapsible **"Varian terarsip"** section
  (`listArchivedVariants` / `restoreVariant`, `GET …/variants/archived` + `POST …/variants/:id/restore`);
  restore reinstates the original SKU and is **refused (block, not auto-suffix)** when a live variant/bundle
  now owns it (`takenSkus` checks variants+bundles; the unique index is the final race guard).
  **Deleting a variant cascades into bundles** (`cascadeBundleComponentRemoval`, inside the deleteVariants +
  deleteProduct tx): its `BundleItem` is dropped from every LIVE bundle, and any bundle left with **0
  components is auto-archived** (it can't be built/sold); already-archived bundles keep their items so a
  restore stays intact. See the Bundles section.
  **QR labels**: `/dashboard/labels` label studio — `listLabelVariants` (paginated; already-printed
  sort last via `labelPrintedAt nulls-first`), prints an A4 grid encoding `barcode ?? sku`.
  `ProductVariant.labelPrintedAt` + `markLabelsPrinted` (`POST /products/variants/printed`) stamp the
  last print; shown in the picker + the shared `QrCodeDialog` (product-detail inline `QrImage`,
  inventory ⋯ action). Endpoints: `GET /products/variants?q=&page=&pageSize=` (label list),
  `POST /products/variants/printed`.
- **inventory** — `Inventory` (fast-read cache: available/reserved/damaged/incoming) +
  **`StockLedger` (append-only = the real source of truth, available-centric)**. Every mutation =
  1 ledger row + 1 Inventory update in ONE tx, **serialized per variant** by `lockAndReadInventory`
  (`pg_advisory_xact_lock(hashtext(variantId))` via **`$executeRaw`** — the lock returns `void`, so
  `$queryRaw` throws "deserialize column of type 'void'"; this is why POS pay once 500'd). The lock
  closes the read-compute-write lost-update on the absolute `availableStock`/`balanceAfter` write.
  `adjustStock` (manual, never negative). Inbound-order
  stock **lifecycle trio** (all `(tx,…)`, available MAY go negative): `applyOrderReserveTx`
  (available−, reserved+; `ORDER_RESERVE`), `applyOrderShipTx` (reserved− only, available unchanged;
  `ORDER_SHIP` delta 0), `applyOrderReleaseTx` (available+, reserved−; `ORDER_RELEASE`). Reserved
  decrements clamp at 0 (+warn) for orders reserved before the lifecycle existed; on-hand = available
  + reserved. Other modules' SoT writes also funnel through here: `applyReturnRestockTx`/
  `applyReturnDamagedTx` (returns), `applyOfflineSaleTx` (POS — available−, `SALE`/`POS`),
  `adjustIncomingTx`/`applyPurchaseReceiveTx` (purchasing — the `incomingStock` bucket). Surfaces: `getDashboard` (KPIs incl. `totalReservedUnits`); `listStockOverview` (now also the
  last movement before→after + `lastAdjustedAt`, via a nested `take:1` ledger include); **reorder
  report** (`inventory-reorder.service` — recency-weighted/EWMA velocity → days-of-cover → suggested
  qty; effective lead time/MOQ resolve variant value → preferred-supplier default (`variant.supplier`,
  soft-deleted ignored) → global; bucketed ledger sums per sub-window); **stock activity
  log** (`inventory-activity.service` — filter reason/source/direction/date + paginate + CSV export).
  Demand reasons for velocity are centralised in `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS` (ORDER_RESERVE + ORDER_RELEASE
  + RETURN + SALE, NOT delta-0 ORDER_SHIP — avoids double-count; nets returns + counts offline POS
  sales). Pure `utils/stock-math.ts` + `utils/reorder-math.ts` are unit-tested. **Stock opname /
  cycle count**: `StockOpname`/`StockOpnameItem` (+ `StockOpnameStatus` DRAFT/COMPLETED/CANCELLED), a
  session at `/dashboard/inventory/opname` — add lines (system qty snapshotted at add) via search OR
  **scan-to-count** (`useOpnameScanner` on an `OPNAME` pairing, **+1 per scan**, `POST /inventory/opname/
:id/scan` → `scanCountItem` resolve+increment in a tx), edit counted inline (a `= sistem` shortcut, live
  variance), then **post** writes each line's variance as a `RECONCILE`/source `MANUAL` ledger row via the
  new `applyReconcileTx(tx,{delta})` (no new ledger reason — RECONCILE existed) + propagates; cancel for a
  draft. Posted/cancelled = read-only variance report. Code `OP00001` per-user. Endpoints under
  `/inventory/opname` (list/create/detail, items upsert/delete, scan, complete, cancel, variants[/resolve]);
  the list endpoint takes optional `search` (code/note contains, case-insensitive) — validator → service
  `where OR` → hook key → URL-synced search box on the list page.
- **reporting** (read-only, "Insights") — profit/margin, per-channel performance, inventory valuation, and
  **dead-stock & ABC**. Dead-stock = in-stock variants idle ≥ a threshold by REAL days-since-last-sale (max
  `SALE`/`ORDER_RESERVE` ledger row) valued at moving-avg cost; ABC = Pareto by net revenue (A/B/C, cumulative
  over positive revenue so return-heavy SKUs fall to C). Pure aggregates unit-tested + per-report CSV; the
  sales reports share `loadSoldLines` (revenue recognition + processed-return netting).
- **marketplace** — connections (`MarketplaceConnection`; now also `lastOrdersPulledAt`) +
  `MarketplaceProduct` (listing snapshot) + `MarketplaceProductMapping` (listing↔variant). Mapping
  is **1:1 on the listing** (`marketplaceProductId @unique`) but ONE variant MAY map to many
  listings — cross-channel sync is by design, do NOT force 1:1. Import via the **env-gated adapter**
  (real `LazadaImportAdapter`/`fetchLazadaListings` for LAZADA, else STUB); auto-map by
  NORMALIZED sku (`utils/sku-match.ts`, NOT edit-distance — `…-M` ≠ `…-L`); non-exact →
  `NEEDS_REVIEW` + sync stays off (per-listing sync is a **Switch**, disabled while NEEDS_REVIEW).
  `mapByExternalRef` upserts a listing (creating its snapshot if never imported) + its mapping.
- **orders** — **multi-store pull** `pullFromConnections(org, actor, { connectionIds?, full? })`
  (default every active store) via an **env-gated order adapter**: real **`LazadaOrderAdapter`**
  (`fetchLazadaOrders` — pages `/orders/get`, batch-hydrates `/orders/items/get`, collapses Lazada's
  one-object-per-unit rows into per-SKU lines; field shapes VERIFY-flagged but paired-test-validated);
  SHOPEE/TOKOPEDIA still the **stub**. Resolve items via mapping → advance the per-order **stock
  lifecycle** (each stage once, idempotent via `Order.inventoryAppliedAt`/`inventoryShippedAt`/
  `inventoryRevertedAt`): RESERVE on PAID, SHIP on SHIPPED/COMPLETED (consumes the reservation; an order
  first seen already shipped reserves then ships), RELEASE on CANCELLED-before-ship. CANCELLED-**after**
  -ship is a return, NOT a release (auto-opens a return, best-effort). Only available changes
  (reserve/release) propagate to OTHER channels (`excludeConnectionId`); ship does not.
  - **INVARIANT — a reserved order's line set is FROZEN.** Re-pulls re-resolve + delete/recreate items
    only while `inventoryAppliedAt` is null; once reserved, carry the persisted **qty + variant +
    unitCost (COGS snapshot)** forward (never wipe/downgrade), and a line that maps later gets a
    **reserve-delta** (don't re-reserve the whole order). Ship/release run off the frozen set. Do NOT
    revert to re-resolving reserved items.
  - **Per-line status** (`NormalizedOrderItem.status`, Lazada per item): a line CANCELLED inside an
    otherwise-shipped order is RELEASED, not consumed. **Seller-SKU fallback** in
    `resolveOrderItemVariantIds` (order line `sku`=seller SKU → `externalSku`) resolves a line the
    `(productId,variantId)` join misses — but an **ambiguous** SKU (same externalSku → 2 variants) stays
    unresolved, never a wrong-variant guess.
  - **Incremental cursor** `MarketplaceConnection.ordersSyncedThrough` (decoupled from the per-provider
    cooldown `lastOrdersPulledAt`): the window is `update_after = cursor − 10min overlap` (30-day first
    backfill); the cursor advances to pull-start **ONLY on a COMPLETE pull** (adapter returns
    `{ orders, complete }`; a throttle/page-cap-truncated pull leaves it so the tail isn't skipped).
    `full:true` ignores the cursor (manual re-sync / fix backlog). Sort = `externalUpdatedAt desc NULLS
    LAST, placedAt, id`.
  - **VPS auto-pull** (runs on the VPS custom server): `runScheduledPull()` (all orgs, `connection.userId` as actor)
    hit by a `server.ts` loopback timer → secret-gated `POST /api/v1/internal/pull-orders`, env
    `ORDERS_AUTO_PULL_INTERVAL_MS` (unset=off). [Batch-3 hardening DONE 2026-06-29: dedicated `INTERNAL_API_SECRET` (falls back to AUTH_SECRET) + per-IP rate-limit + fetch timeout, via shared `lib/api/internal-request.ts`.]
  - `resolveOrderItem` (manual Kaitkan, also from the peek) maps via `mapByExternalRef` + reserves just
    the newly-resolved PAID-order items (idempotent). Per-status detail (SLA/courier/payment/note/cancel
    reason) + per-item photo/link come from `Order.rawPayload` at read-time (`extractOrderMarketplaceMeta`
    /`extractOrderItemMedia`, no schema). Endpoints: `POST /api/v1/orders/pull` (+`full`),
    `/orders/:id/resolve-item`. List has marketplace+store filters. Pull lives on the **Orders** page.
- **fulfillment (Phase 5)** — orders ↔ packing videos are joined by the shared **`noResi`**
  (no FK; matched **case-insensitively** — the resi input is NOT force-uppercased, the scanner is).
  `Order.fulfilledAt` is stamped best-effort when a packing video completes (the recordings complete
  route calls `markFulfilledByResi` — never fails the save). `markFulfilledByResi` stamps ONLY when a
  **COMPLETED Recording exists** for that resi — so marking an order shipped / setting a resi never
  fakes the Fulfillment badge without a video; it just retroactively links a video that already exists.
  `findByResi` resolves the order for a resi
  (the station **pack view** shows its items via `useOrderByResiQuery`); recordings `findByResi` lists
  completed videos for a resi (order/return **evidence**, via `useRecordingsByResiQuery`). Links work
  **both ways**: order/return → packing video, and the recording detail modal + pack view → order.
  Services stay decoupled — composition is at the route/page/hook layer. Endpoints:
  `GET /api/v1/orders/by-resi`, `GET /api/v1/recordings/by-resi`. The **packing departure board**
  (`/dashboard/orders/board`) is a read-only view over the same data: PAID rows ("Terekam — siap
  kirim" when `fulfilledAt`, else "Menunggu dikemas") + recent SHIPPED, polled every 20s by
  `useOrdersBoardQuery` (pageSize 50, shared `orderKeys.list` key) — **NO socket events involved**.
- **returns** — RMA flow (`Return` + `ReturnItem`). A return opens (PENDING) for an order whose goods
  shipped — auto on a detected post-ship cancellation, or manually from the order page — then is
  processed once goods arrive: each line routed to **RESTOCK** (`applyReturnRestockTx`, available+) or
  **DAMAGED** (`applyReturnDamagedTx`, damagedStock+, delta-0 ledger), via the inventory service in one
  tx; restocks propagate to all channels. Ledger reason `RETURN`; restock nets out reorder velocity
  (`SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`). Idempotent (one return per order). Return detail links the packing video by
  `noResi` (dispute evidence). Endpoints: `GET/POST /api/v1/returns`, `/returns/:id`,
  `/returns/:id/process`, `/returns/:id/reject`.
- **sales (offline / POS)** — `Sale` + `SaleItem` (snapshot sku/name/unitPrice), `SalePaymentMethod`
  (CASH/QRIS/TRANSFER), `SaleStatus` (COMPLETED/VOID), code `S00001` per-user. A counter sale
  **decrements the SoT immediately**: one tx creates the sale + lines and calls `applyOfflineSaleTx`
  per line (`available−`, ledger `SALE` / source `POS` / ref = saleId, `note: 'Offline sale'`). Oversell
  is **allowed** (goods are in hand → available MAY go negative). After commit, propagate each sold
  variant's new available to **all** sync-ready channels (selling in-store can't oversell online). The
  POS picker reads ProductVariant read-only (`searchSellableVariants`, active only, by sku/name + price +
  available). `SALE` joins `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`, so offline sales feed reorder velocity. **Scan-to-cart**
  (`usePosScanner`, `scanner-pairing` purpose **POS**): a paired phone scans a product label →
  `resolveSellableVariant` (barcode-then-sku, case-insensitive) → cart line, repeat scan bumps qty, with a
  browser beep. Endpoints: `GET/POST /api/v1/sales`, `/sales/:id`, `/sales/variants?q=`,
  `/sales/variants/resolve?code=`.
- **purchasing (restock / POs)** — `PurchaseOrder` + `PurchaseOrderItem` (snapshot sku/name + `quantity`/
  `receivedQuantity`/`unitCost`), `PurchaseOrderStatus` DRAFT→ORDERED→PARTIALLY_RECEIVED→RECEIVED/CANCELLED,
  code `PO00001` per-user. **Lights up the `incomingStock` bucket** (the last empty one). Two inventory
  tx-methods (no over-credit): `adjustIncomingTx(tx,{variantId,delta})` — `incomingStock += delta`
  clamped at 0, **NO ledger row** (forecast bucket, available unchanged); `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` —
  `incoming−` (clamped) + `available+`, ledger `RESTOCK` / source `PURCHASE` / ref = PO id (and folds the
  received cost into the variant's **moving-average HPP** via `computeMovingAverageCost`). Lifecycle:
  **create** (`status` DRAFT or ORDERED) — ORDERED → `adjustIncomingTx(+qty)` per line + `totalCost`; a
  **DRAFT reserves nothing** and is freely **edited** (`updatePurchaseOrder` — replaces supplier/note/lines
  wholesale, bundle lines collapse to component variant rows), **placed** (`placePurchaseOrder` DRAFT→ORDERED,
  `adjustIncomingTx(+qty)`, stamps `orderedAt`), or **discarded** (`discardDraftPurchaseOrder`, hard delete);
  edit/place/discard are **DRAFT-only** (server-guarded). **receive** (only ORDERED/PARTIALLY_RECEIVED,
  per-line qty clamped to outstanding) → `receivedQuantity +=` + `applyPurchaseReceiveTx`, recompute status
  (all received → RECEIVED + `receivedAt`, else PARTIALLY_RECEIVED), propagate received variants to **all**
  channels; **cancel** (ORDERED/PARTIALLY) → `adjustIncomingTx(−outstanding)` per line, status CANCELLED
  (already-received units stay in available).
  A PO can link a saved **`Supplier`** (`PurchaseOrder.supplierId`, FK SetNull) via a New-PO typeahead;
  `supplierName` is kept as a denormalized snapshot (org-scoped, soft-delete `Supplier` model + CRUD + a
  "Pemasok" page under Stok; `ProductVariant.supplierId` feeds the reorder fallback; variant `cost` stays
  manual). `searchVariants`
  reads ProductVariant read-only (cost + available + incoming), now **paginated** (`?q=&page=&pageSize=`).
  The reorder report's **"Create PO"** prefills `/dashboard/purchasing/new` from URGENT/SOON suggestions.
  **Scan-to-order** (`usePurchaseScanner`, `scanner-pairing` purpose **PURCHASING**): a paired phone scans
  a product label → `resolvePurchasableVariant` → PO line, repeat scan bumps qty, browser beep. Endpoints:
  `GET/POST /api/v1/purchase-orders`, `/purchase-orders/:id`, `/:id/receive`, `/:id/cancel`,
  `/purchase-orders/variants?q=&page=&pageSize=`, `/purchase-orders/variants/resolve?code=`.

## Outbound sync engine (worker-side) — `packages/queue/src/marketplace-sync/`
SoT change → `enqueuePropagateInventoryStock` (web, best-effort, only if `syncEnabled` mappings
exist) → `propagate-inventory-stock` job (fan-out, idempotent per ledger event) →
`sync-marketplace-stock` job → `executeStockSync` (per-provider rate-limit, push LATEST
available via the provider adapter) → marks `MarketplaceSyncJob` + mapping `lastSyncStatus` +
listing snapshot. Retryable failures throw so BullMQ retries. **Provider fallback (guarded):**
`getMarketplaceStockProvider` returns the `Dev` simulator for an unwired provider ONLY outside
production; in **production** it falls back to `Unwired` (rejects, retryable) so a worker booted
without a live connection's creds fails loudly instead of faking `SYNCED` (silent oversell). The
three provider HTTP clients bound each call with an AbortController **timeout** (default 15s, maps to
a retryable error) so one hung provider can't exhaust the sync workers. `executeStockSync` +
`getMarketplaceStockProvider` are unit-tested in `packages/queue/test` (its own vitest config). **Retry UX (2026-06-16):** a retryable hiccup (e.g. Lazada **code 1002**
sentinel/flow-control, "E501: Update product failed") succeeds on the next attempt, so `failSyncJob`
only sets the user-facing `mapping.lastSyncStatus = FAILED` on **finalFailure** (not each attempt) —
no "sinkronisasi gagal" flash mid-retry; `getInFlightSyncProductIds` counts a retry-pending job
(`FAILED` + `completedAt: null`) as in-flight so the indicator/watcher wait it out.
**Coalescing (shipped 2026-06-16):** AUTO changes pass `{ coalesce: true }` to
`enqueuePropagateInventoryStock` → a STABLE per-(org, variant) jobId (`buildCoalescedPropagateJobId`)
+ a 60s delay (`MARKETPLACE_SYNC_COALESCE_WINDOW_MS`); BullMQ dedups a burst into one delayed propagate
that re-reads LATEST available → one push per variant per window instead of one per change
(`removeOnComplete/Fail: true` frees the jobId). **Manual syncs (`syncNow`, `syncAllListings`) stay
immediate** (no coalesce). Next lever (multi-SKU-per-call batching) = Approach B in
`docs/roadmap/sync-batching.md`, build only when many DISTINCT SKUs change at once.
**Bulk + indicator UI:** "Sinkron semua" on the drift panel (`POST /[id]/sync-all`, shown only when the
drift report has drift) re-pushes all sync-enabled listings. `GET /[id]/sync-status` returns the LISTING
IDS currently in-flight (`getInFlightSyncProductIds`) → per-listing button gating (only the listing being
synced is disabled; OTHER listings stay clickable) + a "sinkronisasi berjalan" indicator. An active watcher
(poll every 1.5s + 6s grace, armed on a manual sync) makes the drift re-check + auto-close + status
revalidation deterministic even for fast jobs. A CONFIRMED mapping (manual map / order-resolve / EXACT
auto-map) auto-enables `syncEnabled` (NEEDS_REVIEW stays off).

## Lazada (REAL adapter + OAuth onboarding) — live-validated 2026-06-14
LAZADA is the only **live-validated** real provider; SHOPEE + TOKOPEDIA now have env-gated real adapter
scaffolds that fall back to the stub when creds unset (**NOT live-verified** — paths/signatures flagged
VERIFY; TOKOPEDIA = TikTok Shop Open API v202309 since the standalone Tokopedia API is terminated, needs
`shop_cipher` via the new `MarketplaceConnection.externalShopCipher` column; both have
`/api/v1/marketplaces/{shopee,tokopedia}/oauth/authorize+callback` + new `SHOPEE_*`/`TOKOPEDIA_APP_*` env;
detail: `docs/roadmap/shopee-tokopedia-integration.md`). Lazada signer (HMAC-SHA256, prepend apiPath, UPPER
hex), REST client, import (`/products/get`), stock-push (**`/product/stock/sellable/update`**, POST +
XML, **absolute** `SellableQuantity`), token helpers (`exchangeLazadaCode`/`refreshLazadaToken`) and
`buildLazadaSellableStockPayload` all live in **`@palka/marketplace-providers`** (shared web+worker). The import/stock adapters are **env-gated**:
real only when `LAZADA_APP_KEY`+`LAZADA_APP_SECRET` are set, else fall back to the stub.
- **OAuth onboarding (multi-seller):** each org connects its own shop. `GET /marketplaces/lazada/oauth/
authorize` (gated `marketplace.manage`) → encrypted `state` (org+actor sealed with
  `MARKETPLACE_ENCRYPTION_SECRET`, 15-min TTL, pure codec `utils/oauth-state.ts`) → `auth.lazada.com`.
  `GET …/oauth/callback` is **PUBLIC** (the redirect may not carry the Palka cookie — state is the
  authority) → exchange code → `marketplaceServerService.upsertOAuthConnection` (create / reactivate /
  **re-auth refreshes the token**) → redirect `/marketplace?lazada=connected|error` (toasted). Manual
  paste stays as a dev/fallback for providers without OAuth.
- **Token refresh** `POST /marketplaces/:id/refresh` + **Test koneksi** `POST /marketplaces/:id/test`
  (`/seller/get`); buttons on the connection detail (test = Lazada-specific). Env adds `LAZADA_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI`.
  **Token refresh is provider-agnostic**: the sync engine refreshes lazily before use
  (`ensureFreshAccessToken`) + the daily cron covers LAZADA+SHOPEE+TOKOPEDIA (Shopee tokens last ~4h).
- **Dev tooling:** `pnpm lazada:smoke|token|products|stock|seller` (read `.env`/`apps/web/.env.local`).
  `lazada:stock <token> <itemId> <skuId> <qty> [sellerSku]` posts the real sellable/update payload — set a
  SKU to its current value for a safe no-op probe (it's an absolute set).
- **Lazada-side gotchas (cost real time):** (1) app **category is fixed at creation** — use **"Seller
  In-house APP"** (ISV for public), NOT "LazPay Open API" (Wallet-only → no Product API). (2) **`SellerSku`
  is DEPRECATED** for `price_quantity/update` (E0501) → key by **ItemId+SkuId**. (3) token-create/refresh
  fields are at the **top level** of the envelope, not under `data`. (4) ISV/in-house dev apps must
  **whitelist the seller short code** (Auth Management). (5) callback must be **https** → ngrok in dev.
  (6) gateway must match the seller's **region** (ID=`api.lazada.co.id/rest`). (7) `MARKETPLACE_ENCRYPTION_
SECRET` identical web↔worker. (8) **stock-write FIX (live-validated 2026-06-15):** `/product/price_quantity/
update` returns `SELLER_NOT_PERMITTED`/E501 for **dropshipping-warehouse** sellers — use
  **`/product/stock/sellable/update`** instead (POST + the XML `<SellableQuantity>` payload = **absolute**
  set; a GET → `UnsupportedHTTPMethod`; the simple `skuId`/`sellableQuantity` params → E006). ⚠️ The sibling
  **`/product/stock/sellable/adjust`** takes the SAME XML but applies it as a **DELTA** (live-confirmed:
  0→set5→set5 = 10, and a `-10` brought it back) — do NOT use adjust for sync (it would accumulate). Both
  are stock-only (never touch price). Verified `code:0` + absolute set/read-back on a real dropshipping SKU.
  (9) **multi-warehouse — SHIPPED non-destructive 2026-06-16:** a Lazada SKU can split stock across
  `multiWarehouseInventories[]` (read shape: `warehouseCode`/`sellableQuantity`/…; top-level `quantity` = Σ
  sellableQuantity). **Palka owns exactly ONE warehouse** (per-connection `MarketplaceConnection.syncWarehouseCode`,
  picked in the connection-detail "Gudang sinkron" card from `knownWarehouseCodes` captured at import). The push
  writes `available` to ONLY that warehouse via a **single-entry** `<MultiWarehouseInventories><MultiWarehouse
Inventory><WarehouseCode/><Quantity/></…>` block and **OMITS the rest — Lazada leaves omitted warehouses
  untouched (partial update, live-verified)**. NEVER zero a warehouse we don't own (that erases another writer's
  stock — the rejected "Policy A"). The inner element is **`<Quantity>`** (NOT `<SellableQuantity>`), absolute;
  an unknown child element returns `code:0` yet is silently ignored (validate by changing set + read-back).
  `syncWarehouseCode` null ⇒ bare single-warehouse path (unchanged). **Drift compares internal `available` vs the
  SYNC warehouse's own sellable** (shared `resolveSyncWarehouseStock`), not the cross-warehouse sum — so other
  warehouses' real stock isn't mis-read as drift; the storefront total may legitimately exceed our pool. The
  internal multi-location/WMS generalization (Option A is its n=1 case) is scoped in `docs/roadmap/wms-scoping.md`.
- **Deferred:** multi-region per-connection `region`/`baseUrl` (needs migration — currently one env
  `LAZADA_API_BASE_URL`).

## Phase 6 — provider-health + drift reconciliation + token auto-refresh (shipped 2026-06-15)
- **Zero DB migration, observe-only.** Internal `available` is the SoT; drift is only SURFACED, never
  auto-corrected — the only fix is a manual re-push (`syncNow`). Health is computed on-read from existing
  fields; no new tables.
- **`computeStockDrift`** (`@palka/queue/marketplace-sync/drift.ts`, pure, unit-tested in
  `apps/web/test/marketplace/drift.test.ts`): joins mapped listings to a fresh provider pull and classifies
  each `in_sync | over (external > internal = oversell risk) | under | missing_external`, plus an
  `unmappedExternal` count. Lives in `@palka/queue` so the worker job and the web service compute identically;
  the web client only imports the TYPES (erased), never runtime.
- **Web:** `marketplaceHealthService.listHealth/getHealth` (token lifecycle + sync coverage + needs-review +
  failed pushes + recent sync → `ok|warn|danger` tone); `marketplaceReconciliationService.checkDrift` (pulls
  live external via the import adapter, read-only, reuses `findDriftMappedListings` from `@palka/queue`).
  Routes: `GET /api/v1/marketplaces/health` + `/[id]/health` (**marketplace.view**) · `POST /[id]/drift-check`
  (**marketplace.manage** — it calls the provider). UI: a **"Kesehatan & drift"** panel on the connection
  detail (health summary + "Periksa drift" + per-row "Sync sekarang"), dashboard health badges/summary, and a
  `marketplaceUnhealthy` nav pulse (gated by `marketplace.view`).
- **Worker (runs on the VPS):** `MARKETPLACE_RECONCILE` queue runs two daily scheduled
  jobs via job-name routing — `reconcile-marketplace-drift` (per active connection: rate-limited
  `adapter.fetchListings` → `computeStockDrift` → **log** over/under/missing; stub providers return `null` →
  skipped; best-effort per connection) and `refresh-marketplace-tokens` (renews tokens expiring within the
  window for ALL OAuth providers — `REFRESHABLE_PROVIDERS` = LAZADA+SHOPEE+TOKOPEDIA — via the stored refresh
  token, re-seals with `@palka/utils` crypto; complements the sync engine's lazy refresh-before-use
  `ensureFreshAccessToken`). Drift/token data-access (`findActiveConnectionsForDrift`, `findDriftMappedListings`,
  `findConnectionsForTokenRefresh`, `applyRefreshedConnectionTokens`) lives in `@palka/queue`;
  `findDriftMappedListings` is always called with the connection's OWN `organizationId` (no cross-tenant read).
  Adapter calls take **`ProviderShopCredentials = {accessToken, shopId, shopCipher}`** (worker
  `stock-provider.registry.ts` + web import-adapter params): `shopId` is in Shopee/TikTok signatures,
  `shopCipher` (from `MarketplaceConnection.externalShopCipher`) is TikTok-only, Lazada ignores both.
- **Deferred:** a persistent drift audit-log + configurable alert thresholds. (Shopee + Tokopedia OAuth
  callbacks + stock/import adapters scaffolded 2026-06-17 — env-gated, NOT live-verified.)

## Cross-module composition (respect boundary §3)
- catalog→inventory ONLY via the inventory service (no cross-table writes). orders→inventory via
  the lifecycle trio (`applyOrderReserveTx`/`ShipTx`/`ReleaseTx`); orders→returns via its service
  (auto-open). returns→inventory via `applyReturnRestockTx`/`DamagedTx` and reads Order/OrderItem
  read-only. sales→inventory via `applyOfflineSaleTx`; purchasing→inventory via `adjustIncomingTx`/
  `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` — both read ProductVariant read-only for their pickers and propagate to
  ALL channels after commit (a counter sale or restock moves sellable everywhere). A module may import
  another module's HOOKS/types but NOT its components — cross-module UI composition lives at the APP
  layer (e.g. `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/products/[id]/product-detail-view.tsx` wires catalog
  `ProductDetail` + inventory `AdjustStockDialog`; the reorder report's "Create PO" links into
  purchasing). The variant picker reuses inventory `useStockOverviewQuery`.

## Gotchas (learned the hard way)
- **Two R2 buckets, PER-BUCKET public URLs.** Recordings bucket is **PRIVATE** (playback via presigned
  GET); variant images live in a **separate PUBLIC** bucket. Env: `R2_RECORDINGS_BUCKET_NAME` +
  `R2_PUBLIC_URL` (recordings) · `R2_PRODUCTS_BUCKET_NAME` + `R2_PRODUCTS_PUBLIC_URL` (products). Each
  bucket has its **own** public base; the object URL is `<base>/<key>` with **NO bucket name in the
  path** — r2.dev binds one domain per bucket and serves at the root. Do NOT do `${base}/${bucket}/${key}`
  (it returns 400 → `ERR_BLOCKED_BY_ORB`, image won't render — a reverted dead end). Keys: recordings
  `{userId}/{y}/{m}/file`, products `{userId}/{file}` (`generateProductImageKey`); `isUserStorageKey` =
  `startsWith('{userId}/')`. Image upload is `POST /uploads/presign-image` (client compresses to WebP
  ≤1600px via `utils/compress-image.ts`) → PUT to R2 → `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId/image`
  (stores key + server-computed public URL). `apply-r2-cors` covers both buckets (PUT for upload only;
  `<img>` GET needs no CORS). `imageUrl` is computed at upload time, so changing the URL scheme means
  old rows keep stale URLs → re-upload.
- **BullMQ custom jobId CANNOT contain `:`** → job-id builders use `-` (DB idempotency keys keep `:`).
- A real provider adapter needs the **DECRYPTED token** → lift marketplace token-crypto into a
  shared `@palka/*` package (the engine passes the encrypted token; stubs ignore it).
- A running dev server (`tsx watch server.ts`) holds the Prisma query-engine DLL on Windows →
  `prisma generate` fails `EPERM`. Stop it before generate/migrate; restart after. BUT an
  index-only / no-client-change migration can run with `prisma migrate dev --skip-generate`
  WITHOUT stopping the dev server (only `generate` overwrites the locked DLL).
- `next build` intermittently fails `Failed to collect page data for /<page>` while node procs
  run (a `.next` file-lock flake) — just re-run; not a code error.
- `server-only` services can't be imported into a worker-context `tsx` script without
  `node --conditions=react-server` + the web tsconfig.
- Typed routes: after adding a new `app/**/page.tsx`, `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc`) fails on `Route`
  literals until `next build` regenerates `.next/types`. Build first, then typecheck.

