## Paginated tables (shared)
Inventory overview, the label picker, and the New-PO product picker use `usePagination` +
`TablePagination` (rows-per-page 10/20/50/100, resets to page 1). The label + PO pickers are
**server-paginated** (service returns `PaginatedResult`, route forwards `page`/`pageSize`); inventory
paginates client-side over its capped overview. See `50-ui-design-system.mdc`.

## Bundles (a shortcut, NOT a stock variant)
A **`Bundle`** (`Bundle`/`BundleItem` tables; own sku/barcode/price/image/labelPrintedAt) groups several
variants for buy/sell — it is NOT a `ProductVariant`, holds NO stock, and never appears in product/inventory
lists. Stock + accounting stay per component variant; the bundle is only a one-line / one-scan shortcut in
**New Sale (POS)** and **New PO**. Bundle logic lives in the catalog module's **`bundle-server.service.ts`**
(`bundleServerService`): CRUD + `resolveBundles(bundleIds)` / `resolveBundleByCode` + image +
`listBundleLabels`/`markBundleLabelsPrinted` + `cascadeBundleComponentRemoval(tx,…)`; sales/purchasing
import `bundleServerService` (never the tables). Shared helpers (`takenSkus`/`deleteStorageObject`/
`isUniqueConstraintError`) live in `catalog/utils`.
**Selling/buying explodes a bundle into per-component `SaleItem`/`PurchaseOrderItem` rows at create time**
(`quantity = bundleQty × perBundleQty`), each tagged with `bundleName`, so receive / partial-receive / incoming
/ void / propagate reuse the existing per-row paths unchanged. The single bundle price (POS) / cost (entered
per-PO) is **allocated across components proportional to each component's standard price/cost** (pure
`allocateBundleUnitAmounts`, integer minor units) so per-variant revenue/COGS stay correct. `available` =
`computeBuildableQty` = min(floor(component.available / per-bundle qty)). SKU is unique across **bundles AND
variants** (shared scan namespace; resolver tries variant then bundle). POS oversell warnings accumulate per
variant across the cart. A bundle has an **`isActive`** flag (toggled on its detail) — inactive bundles are
hidden from the POS/PO Bundling pickers and don't resolve from a scan (the Bundles list tags them "Inactive").
Bundles have their own QR labels (labels studio "Bundles" tab; ⋯ "Show QR code" on the list also stamps
`labelPrintedAt`). Marketplace orders are NOT bundle-aware (deferred). UI: `/dashboard/bundles` pages +
`BundleComponentsField` + `BundleImage`. Sale + PO detail GROUP a bundle's exploded lines under a
"Bundle · {name}" header.

**Bundle archive (soft-delete, `Bundle.deletedAt`).** Distinct from `isActive`: `deletedAt` is the archive
flag, `isActive` is the separate visibility toggle. Manual delete now **archives** (`deleteBundle`) — it
frees the SKU (`archivedSku`, same mangle as variants), keeps the composition + image, and is **restorable**;
hard-delete is gone. **Every bundle read filters `deletedAt: null`** (list, labels, `resolveBundles`,
`resolveBundleByCode`, `buildBundleDetail`, `assertBundleOwned`, `assertBundleSkuAvailable`,
`markBundleLabelsPrinted`, and the `takenSkus` clash check). A **"Bundel terarsip"** collapsible on the
bundles dashboard restores via `listArchivedBundles` / `restoreBundle` (`GET …/bundles/archived` +
`POST …/bundles/:id/restore`); restore un-mangles the SKU and is **refused** when a live variant/bundle now
owns it (same block-not-suffix rule as variants). **Auto-archive on variant delete**: when a component
variant is soft-deleted, `cascadeBundleComponentRemoval` removes its `BundleItem` from every live bundle and
archives any bundle left with **0 components** (it can no longer be built/sold). A 0-component bundle that is
later restored comes back empty and is re-filled on the edit screen (the update validator requires ≥1
component). Delete copy across the dashboard + bundle detail says "arsipkan", not "hapus".

